This paper focuses on software engineering (SE) aspects of REST API testing, specifically on security testing. Therefore, cs.SE is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the potential vulnerabilities of the tested system, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper uses techniques such as dynamic analysis and inference, which are related to programming languages (cs.PL) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the scalability of the testing approach, which is related to distributed computing (cs.DC).
